o the heck is General Smedly Butler? I do an Internet search on this vaunted authority on American Imperialism and all I find are the same quotes, most of them on various crackpot websites dedicated to the vast conspiracy against legalization of marijuana and its hemp by-products.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://hqinet001.hqmc.usmc.mil/HD/Historical/Whos_Who/Butler_SD.htm">hqinet001.hqmc.usmc.mil/H...ler_SD.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Major General Smedley Darlington Butler, one of the most colorful officers in the Marine Corps' long history, was one of the two Marines who received two Medals of Honor for separate acts of outstanding heroism. <br>
&quot;<br>
<br>
yea, that's  a real crackpot link, usmc history and museums division :P<br>
<br>
<br>
Here is one particularly damaging quote:<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;1941. Quote from a private memorandum between the Council on Foreign Relations and the State Department:<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;If war aims are stated which seem to be concerned solely with Anglo-American imperialism - they will offer little to people in the rest of the world...The interests of other people should be stressed....This would have a better propaganda effect.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
cited in Lawrence Shoup and Warren Minter, Imperial Brain Trust: the council on foreign relations and US Foreign Policy (New York, Monthly Review 1977) p 130.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
When dealing with history, you can never ever get 'The Truth'.  But we can sure as hell sift thru the evidence and try to get as close to the truth as possible.  And just as you may accuse my sources of being 'liberal bias' I can say the same about republican and or industry funded media as well.  And what's that old saying?  'History is written by the victors.'  So the prudent historian should study both sides of any equation, and through cross referencing, arrive at the closest 'version' of the the truth.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;&quot;Historical facts&quot;? Sez who? You? Or the people being quoted---who incidentally are not named in any of these &quot;actual quotes.&quot;<br>
<br>
I actually named the author of every quote in my post on page 7 of this thread. I can provide you with citations for everything I've just been lazy. Was waiting for someone to ask :P <br>
<br>
Also, regarding my 'historical facts' and 'quotes' I havent seen you provide anything other than your 'opinion'.  Which quite honestly sounds knee jerk and overly 'patriotic'.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
P.S.  &quot;The guy served 33 years in the Marines and THEN the veil lifted from his eyes and realization dawned that he was serving as THE TOOL OF AMERICAN IMPERIALISM?!&quot;<br>
<br>
Economic Imperialism actually.  <br>
<br>
