More Quotes from WW2:<br>
<br>
 "This is a fight between a free world and a slave world." <br>
- Vice President Henry A. Wallace <br>
<br>
"It is the function of the Navy to carry the war to the enemy so that it will not be fought on U.S. soil." <br>
- Admiral Chester W. Nimitz, Commander in Chief of the Pacific Fleet <br>
<br>
"It is my earnest hope - indeed the hope of all mankind - that from this solemn occasion a better world shall emerge out of the blood and carnage of the past, a world found upon faith and understanding, a world dedicated to the dignity of man and the fulfillment of his most cherished wish for freedom, tolerance and justice." <br>
- General Douglas Macarthur, Supreme Allied Commander of South-West Pacific (1945) <br>
<br>
<br>
