Oh and some fun quotes just for shits and giggles:<br>
<br>
"The Axis Powers and France have an identical interest in seeing the defeat of England accomplished as soon as possible. Consequently, the French Government will support, within the limits of its ability, the measures which the Axis Powers may take to this end." <br>
- Marshal Henri Philippe Pétain, Chief of State of Vichy France<br>
<br>
 "I declare that the French Government has ordered me to sign these terms of armistice... Forced by the fate of arms to cease the struggle in which we were engaged on the side of the Allies, France sees imposed on her very hard conditions. France has the right to expect in the future negotiations that Germany show a spirit which will permit the two great neighboring countries to live and work in peace." <br>
- General Huntziger (1940, after the signing of the armistice) <br>
